### Resolve Node.js Module Aliases in Next.js Turbopack

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/upgrading/version-16.mdx

Configures `turbopack.resolveAlias` in `next.config.ts` to provide a fallback for Node.js native modules like `fs` when imported in client-side code. This helps prevent 'Module not found' errors by mapping the module to an empty file, although refactoring client code to avoid such imports is recommended.

```typescript
import type { NextConfig } from 'next'

const nextConfig: NextConfig = {
  turbopack: {
    resolveAlias: {
      fs: {
        browser: './empty.ts', // We recommend to fix code imports before using this method
      },
    },
  },
}

export default nextConfig
```

