### Configure Lightning CSS for Next.js Webpack

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/05-config/01-next-config-js/useLightningcss.mdx

This configuration enables or disables experimental Lightning CSS support in Next.js for projects using webpack. Setting `useLightningcss` to `true` disables PostCSS, while `false` (the default) keeps PostCSS active. This option is ignored when using Turbopack, as Turbopack defaults to Lightning CSS.

```TypeScript
import type { NextConfig } from 'next'

const nextConfig: NextConfig = {
  experimental: {
    useLightningcss: false, // default, ignored on Turbopack
  },
}

export default nextConfig
```

```JavaScript
/** @type {import('next').NextConfig} */
const nextConfig = {
  experimental: {
    useLightningcss: true, // disables PostCSS on webpack
  },
}

module.exports = nextConfig
```

