### Configure bundle analyzer in next.config.js

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/package-bundling.mdx

Set up the bundle analyzer plugin in your Next.js configuration file. The analyzer runs when the ANALYZE environment variable is set to 'true', generating an interactive report of bundle sizes.

```javascript
/** @type {import('next').NextConfig} */
const nextConfig = {}

const withBundleAnalyzer = require('@next/bundle-analyzer')({
  enabled: process.env.ANALYZE === 'true',
})

module.exports = withBundleAnalyzer(nextConfig)
```

